meanings.definition: Plural form of Jacobus. A former English gold coin worth 25 shillings, named after King James I.
meanings.english_definition: Plural of Jacobus. An English gold coin worth 25 shillings, named after King James I.

examples.translation: 彼は古いJacobus金貨を集めていた。

etymology.value: From Jacobus, the Latinized form of James, referring to King James I of England, during whose reign the coin was first minted.
